SIMPLE: incinerate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incinerate
<hw>In*cin"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[LL. <ets>incineratus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>incinerare</ets> to incinerate; L. pref. <ets>in-</ets> in
+ <ets>cinis</ets>, <ets>cineris</ets>, ashes.]</ety> <def>Reduced to
ashes by burning; thoroughly consumed by fire.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incinerate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Incinerate
<hw>In*cin"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Incinerated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Incinerating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To
burn to ashes; to consume by fire; to burn.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is the fire only that <qex>incinerates</qex> bodies.</q>
<rj><qau>Boyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incineration</ent>⟦br⟧
